<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="160" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,710,1582]" pageId="1" pageNumber="160">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,710,735]" pageId="1" pageNumber="160">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Forewing length 
<quantity box="[480,579,711,735]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="160" unit="mm" value="5.5" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="5.0">5–6 mm</quantity>
; hindwing length 
<quantity box="[789,888,711,735]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="160" unit="mm" value="4.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="4.0">4–5 mm</quantity>
. Frons with a brown W-shaped mark (
<figureCitation box="[1338,1405,711,735]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1977,2000]" captionTargetBox="[165,1430,195,1938]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,195,1953]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Spiroberotha sanctarosae. a, head and thorax, lateral; b, male terminalia, lateral; c, head, frontal; d, thorax, dorsal; e, wing venation." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/218306/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="160">
Fig. 
<number box="[1393,1405,711,735]" pageId="1" pageNumber="160" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
c). Scape pale brown, densely covered ventrally with long, brown or ocher setae (
<figureCitation box="[1047,1112,747,771]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1977,2000]" captionTargetBox="[165,1430,195,1938]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,195,1953]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Spiroberotha sanctarosae. a, head and thorax, lateral; b, male terminalia, lateral; c, head, frontal; d, thorax, dorsal; e, wing venation." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/218306/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="160">
Fig. 
<number box="[1100,1112,747,771]" pageId="1" pageNumber="160" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
c). Notal region with a wide pale longitudinal band, lateral borders brown; setae relatively long, scattered, with dark brown bases (
<figureCitation box="[1336,1403,784,808]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1977,2000]" captionTargetBox="[165,1430,195,1938]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,195,1953]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Spiroberotha sanctarosae. a, head and thorax, lateral; b, male terminalia, lateral; c, head, frontal; d, thorax, dorsal; e, wing venation." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/218306/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="160">
Fig. 
<number box="[1392,1403,784,808]" pageId="1" pageNumber="160" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
d). Fore- and hindwing weakly falcate, lacking long and abundant pilosity in alcohol; forewing veins speckled with small brown spots that extend into the membrane (
<figureCitation box="[725,790,858,882]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1977,2000]" captionTargetBox="[165,1430,195,1938]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,195,1953]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Spiroberotha sanctarosae. a, head and thorax, lateral; b, male terminalia, lateral; c, head, frontal; d, thorax, dorsal; e, wing venation." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/218306/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="160">
Fig. 
<number box="[779,790,858,882]" pageId="1" pageNumber="160" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
e); a single crossvein in the radial field; pterostigma pale reddish brown; dark brown spots on the base of Rs + MA and crossvein r-rs; 
<number box="[1017,1054,895,919]" pageId="1" pageNumber="160" value="6.0" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="5.0">5-7</number>
inner gradate crossveins, aligned, some brown pigmented; a single outer gradate crossvein. Hindwing membrane hyaline, except for a small brown spot on the Sc area, near to pterostigma (
<figureCitation box="[635,701,968,992]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1977,2000]" captionTargetBox="[165,1430,195,1938]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,195,1953]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Spiroberotha sanctarosae. a, head and thorax, lateral; b, male terminalia, lateral; c, head, frontal; d, thorax, dorsal; e, wing venation." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/218306/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="160">
Fig. 
<number box="[690,701,968,992]" pageId="1" pageNumber="160" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
e); three crossveins in the radial field; pterostigma pale brown. Ectoproct + tergite 
<number box="[372,386,1005,1029]" pageId="1" pageNumber="160" value="9.0">9</number>
with posterior region densely covered with brown setae; posteroventral margin with curved projections, directed inward (Fig, 
<number box="[540,555,1042,1066]" pageId="1" pageNumber="160" value="2.0">2</number>
b); posterior margins of sternites 
<number box="[935,949,1042,1066]" pageId="1" pageNumber="160" value="8.0">8</number>
and 
<number box="[1007,1021,1042,1066]" pageId="1" pageNumber="160" value="9.0">9</number>
each with pair of lateral projections with a single spur or seta at the apex (
<figureCitation box="[581,649,1079,1103]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1912,1935]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,194,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,194,1891]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Spiroberotha sanctarosae. a, male terminalia, lateral; b, male terminalia, ventral; c, male genitalia, lateral; d, paramere-mediuncus complex, ventral; e, mediuncus and hypandrium internum; f, hypandrium internum. Abreviations: gs, gonarcus; gx 9, gonocoxites 9; hi, hypandrium internum; mu, mediuncus; T 9 + e, tergite nine + ectoproct; T, tergites; S, sternites. Scale bars = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/218307/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="160">
Fig. 
<number box="[634,649,1079,1103]" pageId="1" pageNumber="160" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
b), the first strongly curved dorsad, the second directed caudally (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1912,1935]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,194,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,194,1891]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Spiroberotha sanctarosae. a, male terminalia, lateral; b, male terminalia, ventral; c, male genitalia, lateral; d, paramere-mediuncus complex, ventral; e, mediuncus and hypandrium internum; f, hypandrium internum. Abreviations: gs, gonarcus; gx 9, gonocoxites 9; hi, hypandrium internum; mu, mediuncus; T 9 + e, tergite nine + ectoproct; T, tergites; S, sternites. Scale bars = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/218307/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="160">
Fig. 
<number box="[151,166,1115,1139]" pageId="1" pageNumber="160" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
a, b). Mediuncus coiled, spiral-like, forming 
<number box="[697,760,1115,1139]" pageId="1" pageNumber="160" value="3.75" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="3.5">3.5–4</number>
turns; apices of ninth gonocoxites convergent very close together (Fig. c, d); hypandrium internum triangular (
<figureCitation box="[749,817,1152,1176]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1912,1935]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,194,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,194,1891]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Spiroberotha sanctarosae. a, male terminalia, lateral; b, male terminalia, ventral; c, male genitalia, lateral; d, paramere-mediuncus complex, ventral; e, mediuncus and hypandrium internum; f, hypandrium internum. Abreviations: gs, gonarcus; gx 9, gonocoxites 9; hi, hypandrium internum; mu, mediuncus; T 9 + e, tergite nine + ectoproct; T, tergites; S, sternites. Scale bars = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/218307/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="160">
Fig. 
<number box="[802,817,1152,1176]" pageId="1" pageNumber="160" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
f).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,710,1582]" pageId="1" pageNumber="160">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,436,1189,1214]" pageId="1" pageNumber="160">Adult flight period.</emphasis>
Adults were collected during March and September. 
<taxonomicName box="[1053,1220,1190,1213]" class="Insecta" family="Berothidae" genus="Spiroberotha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="160" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sanctarosae">
<emphasis box="[1053,1220,1190,1213]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="160">S. sanctarosae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been recorded in the literature in the months of December to April (Adams, 
<number box="[873,932,1226,1250]" pageId="1" pageNumber="160" value="1989.0">1989</number>
) and from December through May (Penny, 
<number box="[151,214,1263,1287]" pageId="1" pageNumber="160" value="2002.0">2002</number>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
