<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,710,1582]" pageId="1" pageNumber="160">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,312,1446,1471]" pageId="1" pageNumber="160">Bionomy.</emphasis>
The specimens were collected in Malaise traps, some of them in plantations of the introduced tree 
<taxonomicName box="[151,345,1484,1508]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Gmelina" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="160" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="arborea">
<emphasis box="[151,345,1484,1508]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="160">Gmelina arborea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName box="[360,505,1483,1507]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="160" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Verbenaceae</taxonomicName>
) at the Caribbean region of 
<collectingCountry box="[828,941,1483,1507]" name="Colombia" pageId="1" pageNumber="160">Colombia</collectingCountry>
, where termite colonies of 
<taxonomicName box="[1252,1395,1484,1507]" class="Insecta" family="Rhinotermitidae" genus="Coptotermes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="160" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1252,1395,1484,1507]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="160">Coptotermes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. (
<taxonomicName box="[158,347,1520,1544]" class="Insecta" family="Rhinotermitidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="160" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Rhinotermitidae</taxonomicName>
), 
<taxonomicName box="[368,559,1521,1544]" class="Insecta" family="Termitidae" genus="Microcerotermes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="160" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[368,559,1521,1544]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="160">Microcerotermes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp., and 
<taxonomicName authority="Wasman" authorityName="Wasman" box="[668,962,1520,1544]" class="Insecta" family="Termitidae" genus="Amitermes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="160" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="foreli">
<emphasis box="[668,857,1520,1544]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="160">Amitermes foreli</emphasis>
Wasman
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName box="[979,1104,1520,1544]" class="Insecta" family="Termitidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="160" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Termitidae</taxonomicName>
) are common (Pinzón 
<emphasis box="[1370,1422,1520,1544]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="160">et al</emphasis>
., 
<number box="[151,211,1557,1581]" pageId="1" pageNumber="160" value="1999.0">1999</number>
). Individuals of both locations had pollen grains in their guts.
</paragraph>
